It stresses the importance of controlling bats before starting maintenance work in real estate, as it is possible that the unconscious destruction of one maternal nest can kill up to 400 females and young, which can destroy the entire local population.
Bats are protected and it is illegal to kill, harass, disrupt or destroy their colonies.
Elisabeth Ferrell, the Scottish representative of the Bat Conservation Trust, encourages the public to put their hand in the work and help.
